snippet: Kuwait’s ruler dissolved Parliament on Sunday, a step toward ending political gridlock and calling the second elections this year that could again swing in favor of Islamist-led opposition groups.
abstract: Kuwait's leader Sheik Sabah al-Ahmad al-Sabah dissolves Parliament, in step toward ending political gridlock and calling the second elections this year that could again swing in favor of Islamist-led opposition groups.
lead_paragraph: Kuwait’s ruler dissolved Parliament on Sunday, a step toward ending political gridlock and calling the second elections this year that could again swing in favor of Islamist-led opposition groups.

headline.main: In Bid to End Crisis, Kuwait’s Parliament Is Dissolved
